Virgin May Develop Business for Over 60s, Sunday Express Says

-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 
2011-06-19T13:36:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-19/virgin-may-develop-business-for-over-60s-sunday-express-says.html
Virgin Group Ltd. may develop a
business to target customers over the age of 60, competing with
Saga Group Plc, the  Sunday Express  reported, citing founder
 Richard Branson .  Branson also said his Virgin Money Holdings U.K. Ltd.
business may bid for Northern Rock Plc, and for branches being
sold by  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  in an interview in Miami, the
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in  London  at 
 pdobson2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  